I demonstrate how to create venv on Windows 10 using WSL, and install Ubuntu 20.04 first, then create the venv for my project.

Then I realized that I can try it on Windows 10, it may not work very well, but worth to try and compare.

step 1: create project directory, change to this directory, then create venv

python -m venv env

step 2: install virtualenvwrapper and / or virtualenvwrapper-win

pip install virtualenvwrapper

pip install virtualenvwrapper-win

step 3: start the venv

D:\projects\flask\restfulapidemo1>env\Scripts\activate.bat

That is it, will continue try and see if it works, stay tune.
